{"id": "EUVD-2018-8676", "enisaUuid": "03cb6a14-cdc2-349f-8354-f30d153eb84b", "description": "It was discovered systemd does not correctly check the content of PIDFile files before using it to kill processes. When a service is run from an unprivileged user (e.g. User field set in the service file), a local attacker who is able to write to the PIDFile of the mentioned service may use this flaw to trick systemd into killing other services and/or privileged processes. Versions before v237 are vulnerable.", "datePublished": "2019-01-14T22:00:00", "dateUpdated": "2024-08-05T10:39:58", "baseScore": 4.4, "baseScoreVersion": "3.0", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.0/AV:L/AC:H/PR:L/UI:R/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://www.suse.com/security/cve/CVE-2018-16888.html", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHBA-2020:0547", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2019:2091", "https://ubuntu.com/security/CVE-2018-16888", "https://linux.oracle.com/cve/CVE-2018-16888.html", "https://security.netapp.com/advisory/ntap-20190307-0007/", "https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=CVE-2018-16888", "https://lists.apache.org/thread.html/5960a34a524848cd722fd7ab7e2227eac10107b0f90d9d1e9c3caa74%40%3Cuser.cassandra.apache.org%3E", "https://usn.ubuntu.com/4269-1/"], "aliases": ["CVE-2018-16888"], "assigner": "redhat", "epss": 0.16, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "2d7dc96c-3202-38bd-806d-e18342d09278", "product": {"name": "systemd"}, "product_version": "v237"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "eb275627-734a-36f5-a9d5-c979c55a3682", "vendor": {"name": "The systemd Project"}}], "isExploited": false}